      • isAdmissible

        protected boolean isAdmissible(int i,
                               int j)
        Returns a boolean flag stating if this sudoku is admissible around the cell (i, j). False indicates that there exists at least one conflict in the i-th row or the j-th column or the subsquare containing the cell (i, j).
        Parameters:
        i - row index
        j - column
        Returns:
        boolean flag stating if this sudoku is admissible around (i, j)

      • isGroupAdmissible

        protected boolean isGroupAdmissible(java.util.List<java.lang.Byte> group)
        A helper method for isAdmissible() method. Returns a boolean flag indicating if the given group of numbers (row, column, or subsquare) is admissible (i.e. contains no conflicts).
        Parameters:
        group - group to be checked
        Returns:
        boolean flag indicating if given group of numbers is admissible
